Property.preferredName: Post Hematopoietic Cell Transplantation Course Two Definition Fulfill
Property.preferredDefinition: Happening at a time subsequent to a reference time; later in time or order.:A therapeutic procedure that involves the transplantation of hematopoietic stem cells from a donor to a patient with a myeloid or lymphocytic malignancy.:Passage through time; duration; a systematic or/and orderly succession; a sequence, e.g. course of treatment; a mode of action or behavior; natural development, typical manner of proceeding.:A natural number greater than 1 and less than 3 and the quantity that it denotes: the sum of one and one.:A concise explanation of the meaning of a word or phrase or symbol.:Satisfy the requirements or expectations of.

Concepts.definition: Happening at a time subsequent to a reference time; later in time or order.

A therapeutic procedure that involves the transplantation of hematopoietic stem cells, either with the patient as their own donor or from a donor to a patient. This can be used for treatment of malignant and non-malignant diseases.
Passage through time; duration; a systematic or/and orderly succession; a sequence, e.g. course of treatment; a mode of action or behavior; natural development, typical manner of proceeding.
A natural number greater than 1 and less than 3 and the quantity that it denotes: the sum of one and one.
A concise explanation of the meaning of a word or phrase or symbol.
Satisfy the requirements or expectations of.
